Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Heat the oil in an ovenproof frying pan and sear the chicken breast on all sides until golden-brown, about 4-5 minutes.Add the garlic cloves, chopped chillies and honey to the pan, stir, and transfer to the oven to cook for 8-10 minutes, or until the chicken is completely cooked through.To serve, place the chicken onto a serving plate with the green beans and drizzle over the pan juices. Scatter with toasted almonds and serve.